value.value: The inflection that extends along the dorsal margin of the pronotum and supports the anterior inflection of the mesoscutum.
The area that is located posterodorsally of the well-sclerotized lateral propleural area and usually differs from it in sculpture.
The ridge that is marginal or submarginal, extends along the dorsal margin of the propleuron and corresponds to the site of origin of the lateral propleuro-postoccipital muscle.
The inflection that extends along the dorsal margin of the propodeum and accommodates the metanotum.
The sclerite that is located dorsally between the penisvalvae.
The salivarial muscle that inserts proximodorsally on the salivary duct.
The apodeme that arises anterodorsally from the anterior tentorial arm and extends to the anterior wall of the cranium.
The apical tooth of mandible that is located closest to the clypeus.
The anatomical line that is located between the dorsum and the pleuron.

The cupulo-gonostyle/volsella complex muscle that arises from the dorsolateral part of the cupula, just laterally of the site of origin of the dorsomedian cupulo-gonostipal muscle, and inserts on the dorsolateral part of the gonostipes.
The cupulo-gonostyle/volsella complex muscle that inserts medially on the dorsal region of the gonostyle/volsella complex.
The pit that is located at the proximal end of the dorsal carina on the abdominal tergum 2.
The area of the segment that is dorsal.
The cavitated compound organ that is canal-like, layered with epithelial cells and leads from an exocrine gland or organ.
The duct that connects the vas deferens with the endophallus and is ectodermal in origin.
The anatomical cluster that is composed of the sclerites and muscles of the external male genitalia.
The margin that extends along the border of two areas that are oriented differently.
The flagellomere that is located proximally on the flagellum and lacks longitudinal sensilla.
The anatomical space that surrounds the plate-like structure in a multiporous plate sensillum.
The procuticle that is not tanned (sclerotised, proteins scarcely crosslinked) and located between the Schmidt's layer and the exocuticle.
The conjunctiva that connects the gonopore with the penisvalvae.
The carina that delimits posteriorly the epicnemium.
The cuticular invagination that is located at the lateral end of the epicnemial carina.
The scrobe that is located anteroventrally on the mesopectus and accommodates the procoxa.
The area that is located posteroventrally on the propleuron and is delimited anteriorly by the epicoxal sulcus.
The sulcus that is dorsal to the coxal foramen.
The suture that is Y-shaped and located dorsally on the cranium.
The epithelium that is located in the integument and composed of epidermal cells.
The area that is located on the pleuron and is delimited anteriorly by the pleural sulcus.
The conjunctiva that extends between the distal margin of the labrum and the proximal boundary of the cibarium.
The lobe that is located distally on the epipharyngeal wall.
The flange that is located on abdominal tergum 10, between the cerci.
The area that is located on the pleuron anteroventrally of the pleural sulcus.
The notch that is located on the ventral margin of the clypeus.
The ridge that corresponds to the epistomal sulcus.
The sulcus that extends along the epistomal line.
The carina that is vertical, crosses the pronotum and separates the lateral pronotal area from the median pronotal area.

The apodeme that is lateral, located medially on the penisvalva and corresponds to the sites of insertion of the lateral and distoventral gonostyle/volsella complex-penisvalval muscle and the parossiculo-penisvalval muscles.
The sclerite that is located on the thoracic sternum posteriorly of the spinasternum.
The area that is highly sculptured and surrounds the opening of a gland.
The procuticle that is tanned (sclerotised, proteins are highly crosslinked) and located between the endocuticle and epicuticle.
The appendage that is connected to the body by the cupulo-S9 muscles.
The anatomical cluster that is composed of the gonostipites and volsellae.
The labial muscle that arises from the prementum and inserts on the first sclerite of the labial palp.
The cuticle that is discarded after a molt.
The area that extends from the median ocellus to the oral foramen.
The area that is concave, narrow, often finely and densely pubescent and extends along the inner orbit.
The line that extends along the border of the eye and lower face.
The pit that overlaps with the facial apodeme.
